image_analysis.description: A photograph of a utility or mechanical room. The image shows complex plumbing and HVAC equipment. On the left, there are large insulated pipes, gauges, and valves. A grey control box is mounted on the wall. In the center, there is a wall-mounted faucet over a small tiled area. A thin copper pipe runs horizontally across the back wall. Above, a large rectangular HVAC unit with a blue filter is mounted to the ceiling. A framed document or chart is hanging on the wall.
image_analysis.layout: The image is a wide-angle photograph of an interior utility space.

document_metadata.subject: Mechanical room or utility area documentation

notes: The text on the framed document on the wall is illegible due to distance and focus. The labels 'DRAIN' appear on green tape wrapped around copper piping.
